Based on the provided summary and the specified concern (data_flow) and behavior (static, dynamic), I'll create a PlantUML sequence diagram that illustrates the data flow in the serverdevcamp_camp4_quadcore system. This diagram will show both static components and dynamic interactions.

@startuml serverdevcamp_camp4_quadcore

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 20
skinparam maxmessagesize 60

actor User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "AuthServer" as Auth
database Redis
participant "DataPipeline" as Pipeline
participant "DataProcessing" as Processing
database Kafka
database Cassandra
participant "DataSending" as Sending
participant "UserActivity" as Activity

User -> Frontend : Interacts
Frontend -> Gateway : API Request
Gateway -> Auth : Validate JWT

alt Valid Token
    Auth -> Gateway : Token Valid
    Gateway -> Pipeline : Forward Request
    Pipeline -> Kafka : Stream Data
    Kafka -> Processing : Process Data
    Processing -> Cassandra : Store Processed Data
    Cassandra -> Sending : Retrieve Data
    Sending -> Frontend : Send Real-time Data (WebSocket)
    Activity -> Cassandra : Fetch User Activity
    Activity -> Frontend : Send User Activity
else Invalid Token
    Auth -> Gateway : Token Invalid
    Gateway -> Frontend : Unauthorized
end

Frontend -> User : Update UI

